Step 2: Change the instance type
Use the following command to modify the instance type:

bash
Copy
Edit
aws ec2 modify-instance-attribute --instance-id <instance-id> --instance-type "{\"Value\": \"<new-instance-type>\"}"
Example:

bash
Copy
Edit
aws ec2 modify-instance-attribute --instance-id i-1234567890abcdef0 --instance-type "{\"Value\": \"t3.large\"}"
This changes the instance type to the desired type (e.g., t3.large).
